            <h3 class="mb-1 orbitron">Competitive Advantage</h3>
            <p>The website reflects the school in terms of values, attitude towards prospects and acceptance of modern trends. Such a development will give your school a competitive advantage and help you set yourself apart from the competition.</p>
            <p>To make the most of the opportunity, take a look at the websites of other schools in the region. What kind of features do these websites have and what are they missing? A little bit of competition research can help you get inspired. You will easily figure out how to position yourself and create the most appealing persona for your establishment.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-2">
            <h3 class="mb-1 orbitron">Showcase Your School Online</h3>
            <p>Having a website is the heart and soul of every online marketing strategy. The number of people looking for information online is growing all the time. If you lack a sensible online presence, you are missing a great opportunity to advertise your school.</p>
            <p>This type of advertising is highly targeted – you will be reaching people that have a particular interest in the opportunity provided. It is also much more cost-efficient than paying for traditional promotion like television ad spots or outdoor billboards.</p>
            <p>Online marketing has many faces. It can come in the form of a content-based strategy, social media marketing, YouTube videos or pay per click (PPC) campaigns. To make use of these opportunities, however, you need a landing page.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-2">
            <h3 class="mb-1 orbitron">Improve The Brand Image</h3>
            <p>You also want your brand image to be positive, and you can achieve this through taking the time and care to update a website and provide information to the community. You may be marketing your website online, and an interactive site can ensure that when people arrive at your website, they see your school in the best light.</p>

        </div>
        <div class="mb-2">
            <h3 class="mb-1 orbitron">Your School Website & Staff Recruitment</h3>
            <p>Of course, the benefits of a well-refined school website are not just for parents and pupils. Recruiting suitable school staff has always been one of the biggest challenges facing schools. The school website will always be one of the first place to look for job applicants, and as we learned from our last blog, it takes under 1 second to form an opinion of a webpage after a user lands on it. With this in mind, are you satisfied that your school website conveys the best possible image of your school and would be an attractive proposition for a potential new member of staff?</p>
        </div>
